An elemental follower is capable of all of the
commands listed in 'dhelp follower'.  In addition,
all elementals are magic resistant and capable of
flight, and they also have specific properties:

Air - These elementals are very fast, but physically
weak.  Their magical attack is a lightning spell,
making them useful against water creatures or those
wearing metal armor.  They are healed by lightning
and weak against water attacks and weapon blows.

Earth - These are the strongest but slowest of the
elementals.  Their magical attack, a stone bolt, is
the weakest of the four types, but their melee attacks
are quite strong.  They are resistant to weapon blows
and other forms of physical attack, but weak against
disintegration effects.

Fire - These tend to be the strongest all-around in
combat, with no stats standing out as particularly
strong or weak and a devastating magical firebolt
attack.  They are healed by fire but weak against
water and cold attacks.

Water - Another fairly balanced elemental in terms
of stats, they tend to be stronger but slower than
fire elementals.  Their magical attack is a rush
of water, which both batters and drowns opponents.
They are healed by water attacks and strong against
cold, but weak against fire and lightning.
